01:08:02.938 --> 01:08:04.190
this course will help you.
 

01:08:04.190 --> 01:08:05.730
So here's another one.
 

01:08:05.730 --> 01:08:09.293
You are in a prison and it
doesn't have infinite walls,

01:08:09.293 --> 01:08:11.010
but it's got some walls.
 

01:08:11.010 --> 01:08:12.619
What's your strategy?
 

01:08:12.619 --> 01:08:16.358
I say go ram yourself into that
wall as often as you can,

01:08:16.358 --> 01:08:19.494
because there's a small
probability that you can

01:08:19.494 --> 01:08:22.500
suddenly find yourself on the
other side.

01:08:22.500 --> 01:08:25.578
This is what happens in alpha
decay.

01:08:25.578 --> 01:08:29.105
In alpha decay,
there's helium nuclei sitting

01:08:29.105 --> 01:08:30.630
inside a nucleus.
 

01:08:30.630 --> 01:08:34.168
There's a barrier that keeps it
from coming out of the nucleus,

01:08:34.168 --> 01:08:36.510
but the barrier goes up and
comes down.

01:08:36.510 --> 01:08:38.832
So if you go a certain distance
from the nucleus,

01:08:38.832 --> 01:08:39.800
you're again free.
 

01:08:39.800 --> 01:08:41.970
So the alpha particle does
exactly what I told you.

01:08:41.970 --> 01:08:44.462
It goes rattling back and forth
inside the nucleus and once in a

01:08:44.462 --> 01:08:46.438
while,
it penetrates and comes to the

01:08:46.438 --> 01:08:48.658
other side,
and that's the alpha decay of

01:08:48.658 --> 01:08:49.340
the nucleus.
 

01:08:49.340 --> 01:08:51.238
So this really happens.
 

01:08:51.238 --> 01:08:54.627
It may not happen to you in the
situation I described,

01:08:54.627 --> 01:08:56.800
but the probability is not
zero.

